Managed to make it to the beach one last time in 2023 and this was the find of the day.  It’s about the size of a fist and a giant mystery. Obviously red, purple, and yellow jasper in parts, some quartz and chalcedony too. But I think this might be a jasperized stromatoporoid fossil. 🤷‍♂️
